Math and Statistical SQL Functions

Data Cloud provides several math and statistical SQL functions that you can use in Calculated Insights.

REQUIRED EDITIONS
Available in: Lightning Experience
Abs

The abs function calculates the absolute value of a number. The absolute value is the number without its positive or negative sign.

Syntax

abs (number)

Arguments

ARGUMENT	DESCRIPTION
number	The value or measure field that you want to determine the absolute value for.
Greatest

The greatest function returns the greatest value of all parameters, skipping all null values.

Syntax

SELECT greatest(10, 9, 2, 4, 3);

Arguments

ARGUMENT	DESCRIPTION
exper	arg1, arg2, arg3,
Least

The least function returns the smallest value in the argument list.

Syntax

SELECT least(10, 9, 2, 4, 3);

Arguments

ARGUMENT	DESCRIPTION
exper	arg1, arg2, arg3,
Log

The greatest function returns the logarithm of a number in a specified base.

Syntax

log(base, number)

Arguments

ARGUMENT	DESCRIPTION
base	Value or measure field used as the base of the logarithm
number	Value or measure field that you want to take the logarithm of.
Rand

The rand function returns a random decimal number (distributed values in [0, 1). The function is non-deterministic in the general case.

Syntax

SELECT rand()
SELECT rand(0)


Arguments

ARGUMENT	DESCRIPTION
seed	Optional. If seed is specified, it returns a repeatable sequence of random numbers. If no seed is specified, it returns a random number.
Round

The round function rounds a number to the specified decimal place.

Syntax

SELECT round(2.5, 0);

Arguments

ARGUMENT	DESCRIPTION
exper	Expression that you want to round.
number	Number of decimal places.
Stddev

The stddev function returns the statistical standard deviation of all values in the specified expression.

Syntax

SELECT stddev(col)

Arguments

ARGUMENT	DESCRIPTION
Exper	The expression that you want to calculate.
Exp (Exponential)

The exp function returns a value for e raised to the power of a specified number.

Syntax

exp(number)

Arguments

ARGUMENT	DESCRIPTION
number	The value or measure field that you want to raise to.
Mod

The mod function returns the remainder after expr1/expr2.

Syntax

SELECT MOD(3, 1.8);

Arguments

ARGUMENT	DESCRIPTION
expr1	Number
expr2	Divisor
Count (Exper)

The count function is an aggregate that returns the number of rows.

Syntax

Select count(coumn_name)
